<taxonomicName authority="Hohn., Sber. Akad. Wiss. Wien, Math." box="[136,710,1778,1805]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Phaeoisaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,274,1778,1805]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">Phaeoisaria</emphasis>
Höhn., Sber. Akad. Wiss. Wien, Math.
</taxonomicName>
-naturw. Kl., Abt. 1 118: 330 (1909)
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="158" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1214,1854,1876]" box="[136,1214,1854,1876]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,263,1854,1876]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">
<typeStatus box="[136,186,1854,1875]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">Type</typeStatus>
species
</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Hohn., Sber. Akad. Wiss. Wien, Math." box="[276,870,1854,1876]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Phaeoisaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambusae">
<emphasis box="[276,496,1854,1875]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">Phaeoisaria bambusae</emphasis>
Höhn., Sber. Akad. Wiss. Wien, Math.
</taxonomicName>
-naturw. Kl., Abt. 1 118: 329 (1909)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1922,2093]" lastBlockId="15.[136,1452,158,257]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="158" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,212,1922,1948]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">Notes:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[219,356,1922,1948]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Phaeoisaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[219,356,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">Phaeoisaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, typified by 
<taxonomicName box="[498,657,1922,1948]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Phaeoisaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bambusae">
<emphasis box="[498,657,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">Ph. bambusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, can be easily recognized by its erect, brown, indeterminate synnemata with compact and parallel arrangement of conidiophores, sympodially extending polyblastic, denticulate conidiogenous cells and solitary, septate or aseptate, ellipsoidal, obovoid, fusiform-cylindrical or falcate conidia (
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng, X. L. &amp; Li, W. &amp; Zhang, T. Y." box="[1242,1447,1994,2021]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" pagination="17 - 24" refId="ref11089" refString="Cheng, X. L., Li, W. &amp; Zhang, T. Y. (2014) A new species of Phaeoisaria from intertidal marine sediment collected in Weihai, China. Mycotaxon 127: 17 - 24. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 127.17" type="journal article" year="2014">
Cheng 
<emphasis box="[1324,1374,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reblova, M. &amp; Seifert, K. A. &amp; Fournier, J. &amp; Stepanek, V." box="[136,383,2030,2057]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" pagination="57 - 81" refId="ref17753" refString="Reblova, M., Seifert, K. A., Fournier, J. &amp; Stepanek, V. (2016 a) Newly recognised lineages of perithecial ascomycetes: the new orders Conioscyphales and Pleurotheciales. Persoonia 37: 57 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.3767 / 003158516 X 689819" type="journal article" year="2016">
Réblová 
<emphasis box="[241,294,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">et al</emphasis>
. 2016 
<bibRefCitation author="Rambaut, A. &amp; Drummond, A. J. &amp; Xie, D. &amp; Baele, G. &amp; Suchard, M. A." box="[371,383,2030,2056]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" refId="ref17487" refString="Rambaut, A., Drummond, A. J., Xie, D., Baele, G. &amp; Suchard, M. A. (2018) Tracer v 1.7. Available from: http: // beast. community / tracer (Accessed 8 May 2021)" type="url" year="2018">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, Luo 
<emphasis box="[455,508,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">et al</emphasis>
. 2018). Currently, 23 epithets are listed in the genus, but only eight species are confirmed with molecular data (
<bibRefCitation author="Luo, Z. L. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; Liu, J. K. &amp; Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N. &amp; Jeewon, R. &amp; Bao, D. F. &amp; Bhat, D. J. &amp; Lin, C. G. &amp; Li, W. L. &amp; Yang, J. &amp; Liu, N. G. &amp; Lu, Y. Z. &amp; Jayawardena, R. S. &amp; Li, J. F. &amp; Su, H. Y." box="[496,672,2066,2093]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" pagination="451 - 660" refId="ref16981" refString="Luo, Z. L., Hyde, K. D., Liu, J. K., Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N., Jeewon, R., Bao, D. F., Bhat, D. J., Lin, C. G., Li, W. L., Yang, J., Liu, N. G., Lu, Y. Z., Jayawardena, R. S., Li, J. F. &amp; Su, H. Y. (2019) Freshwater Sordariomycetes. Fungal Diversity 99: 451 - 660. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 019 - 00438 - 1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Luo 
<emphasis box="[550,599,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hyde, K. D. &amp; Norphanphoun, C. &amp; Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N. &amp; Bhat, D. J. &amp; Jones, E. B. G. &amp; Bundhun, D. &amp; Chen, Y. J. &amp; Bao, D. F. &amp; Boonmee, S. &amp; Calabon, M. S. &amp; Chaiwan, N. &amp; Chethana, K. W. T. &amp; Dai, D. Q. &amp; Dayarathne, M. C. &amp; Devadatha, B. &amp; Dissanayake, A. J. &amp; Dissanayake, L. S. &amp; Doilom, M. &amp; Dong, W. &amp; Fan, X. L. &amp; Goonasekara, I. D. &amp; Hongsanan, S. &amp; Huang, S. K. &amp; Jayawardena, R. S. &amp; Jeewon, R. &amp; Karunarathna, A. &amp; Konta, S. &amp; Kumar, V. &amp; Lin, C. G. &amp; Liu, J. K. &amp; Liu, N. G. &amp; Luangsaard, J. &amp; Lumyong, S. &amp; Luo, Z. L. &amp; Marasinghe, D. S. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Niego, A. G. T. &amp; Niranjan, M. &amp; Perera, R. H. &amp; Phukhamsakda, C. &amp; Rathnayaka, A. R. &amp; Samarakoon, M. C. &amp; Samarakoon, S. M. B. C. &amp; Sarma, V. V. &amp; Senanayake, I. C. &amp; Shang, Q. J. &amp; Stadler, M. &amp; Tibpromma, S. &amp; Wanasinghe, D. N. &amp; Wei, D. P. &amp; Wijayawardene, N. N. &amp; Xiao, Y. P. &amp; Yang, J. &amp; Zeng, X. Y. &amp; Zhang, S. N. &amp; Xiang, M. M." box="[683,888,2066,2093]" pageId="14" pageNumber="157" pagination="305 - 1059" refId="ref15106" refString="Hyde, K. D., Norphanphoun, C., Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N., Bhat, D. J., Jones, E. B. G., Bundhun, D., Chen, Y. J., Bao, D. F., Boonmee, S., Calabon, M. S., Chaiwan, N., Chethana, K. W. T., Dai, D. Q., Dayarathne, M. C., Devadatha, B., Dissanayake, A. J., Dissanayake, L. S., Doilom, M., Dong, W., Fan, X. L., Goonasekara, I. D., Hongsanan, S., Huang, S. K., Jayawardena, R. S., Jeewon, R., Karunarathna, A., Konta, S., Kumar, V., Lin, C. G., Liu, J. K., Liu, N. G., Luangsaard, J., Lumyong, S., Luo, Z. L., Marasinghe, D. S., McKenzie, E. H. C., Niego, A. G. T., Niranjan, M., Perera, R. H., Phukhamsakda, C., Rathnayaka, A. R., Samarakoon, M. C., Samarakoon, S. M. B. C., Sarma, V. V., Senanayake, I. C., Shang, Q. J., Stadler, M., Tibpromma, S., Wanasinghe, D. N., Wei, D. P., Wijayawardene, N. N., Xiao, Y. P., Yang, J., Zeng, X. Y., Zhang, S. N. &amp; Xiang, M. M. (2020 a) Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11: 305 - 1059." type="journal article" year="2020">
Hyde 
<emphasis box="[751,800,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="157">et al</emphasis>
. 2020a
</bibRefCitation>
). Five species have been reported from freshwater habitats (
<bibRefCitation author="Luo, Z. L. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; Liu, J. K. &amp; Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N. &amp; Jeewon, R. &amp; Bao, D. F. &amp; Bhat, D. J. &amp; Lin, C. G. &amp; Li, W. L. &amp; Yang, J. &amp; Liu, N. G. &amp; Lu, Y. Z. &amp; Jayawardena, R. S. &amp; Li, J. F. &amp; Su, H. Y." box="[239,419,158,185]" pageId="15" pageNumber="158" pagination="451 - 660" refId="ref16981" refString="Luo, Z. L., Hyde, K. D., Liu, J. K., Maharachchikumbura, S. S. N., Jeewon, R., Bao, D. F., Bhat, D. J., Lin, C. G., Li, W. L., Yang, J., Liu, N. G., Lu, Y. Z., Jayawardena, R. S., Li, J. F. &amp; Su, H. Y. (2019) Freshwater Sordariomycetes. Fungal Diversity 99: 451 - 660. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 019 - 00438 - 1" type="journal article" year="2019">
Luo 
<emphasis box="[293,343,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, we collected a phaeoisaria-like taxon from submerged wood in a small river of 
<collectingRegion box="[166,461,194,220]" country="Thailand" name="Nakhon Phanom" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Nakhon Phanom Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[471,574,194,220]" name="Thailand" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. Phylogenetic analyses confirmed our new collection clustered in 
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1444,194,220]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Phaeoisaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="15" pageNumber="158" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1307,1444,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">Phaeoisaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and represents 
<emphasis box="[304,610,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicName box="[304,606,230,256]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diatrypaceae" genus="Phaeoisaria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Xylariales" pageId="15" pageNumber="158" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="annesophieae">Phaeoisaria annesophieae</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
